cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network model for image quality assessment, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adaptive weighting and the consideration of perceptual properties of the human visual system suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of batch normalization and l2 regularization also suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the use of Euclidean distance and the consideration of image patches suggest a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
